                    Chicken with Rotini Pasta 
Makes 6 servingsTime to Prepare: 0:45Time to Cook: 0:55

Add to Shopping List

Ingredients
1 lbChicken, broilers or fryers, breast, meat and skin, raw
1/4 cupOlive Oil
1 cupOnions, raw
2 cloveGarlic, raw
1 cupTomatoes, red, ripe, raw, year round average
1/2 cupAlcoholic beverage, wine, table, white
1/2 cupSoup, chicken broth, canned, prepared with equal volume water, commercial
4 tblsBasil, fresh
1/2 lbMacaroni, dry, enriched

Directions
1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. Season the chicken with salt and pepper. 2. Bake for 45 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked. 3. Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 30 minutes. 4. Remove and discard the skin from the chicken. 5. Remove the meat from the breast bones and set aside. 6. Tear the chicken meat into bite-sized pieces. 7. Preheat a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat. 8. Add the olive oil, onion and garlic. Saute for 5 minutes or until the onions have softened. 9. Add the chicken meat, tomatoes, wine and chicken stock to the skillet and continue cooking for 5 minutes. Add the fresh basil and cooked pasta. Toss the cooked pasta in the sauce and continue cooking until hot and serve. 





